Package gov.usgs.locator

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AuxLocRef
    Read in auxiliary data to support the Locator.
    CloseOut
    After an event is located, the close out phase computes all the errors and heuristics used to evaluate the location.
    CorrSum
    Support the triage algorithm by holding the sum of correlations among picks for one pick in a sortable way.
    Craton
    Keep track of the geometry of one craton.
    Cratons
    Keep track of the geographic boundaries of continental cratons.
    DeCorr
    Handle the decorrelation of the pick data.
    EllipAxis
    A description of one axis of an error ellipse.
    Event
    Keep all data for one seismic event (earthquake usually).
    GroupComp
    Group comparator.
    HypoAudit
    Audit instances are intended to provide a snapshot of the event at different points in the location process for logging purposes.
    Hypocenter
    Keep all the data for one hypocenter together.
    InitialID
    Before any location iteration or real phase identification takes place, this initial pass ensures that we have something reasonable to work with by emphasizing crust and mantle P waves and manually identified phases.
    LinearStep
    Computing seismic travel times is expensive, so instead set the steepest descent step length using the linear term of a Taylor series.
    Locate
    Locate drives the location of one earthquake.
    LocInput
    Locator inputs needed to relocate an event.
    LocMain
    Test driver for the locator.
    LocOutput
    Locator outputs from an event relocation.
    LocUtil
    Locator static constants and utilities.
    PhaseID
    Associate theoretical seismic phases with observed seismic picks.
    Pick
    Keep all the data for one pick together.
    PickComp
    Pick comparator.
    PickGroup
    Pick groups contain all the picks observed at one station for one event.
    PickInput
    Pick inputs needed to relocate an event.
    PickOutput
    Pick outputs after a relocation.
    Restimator
    Rank-sum estimator implementation for the NEIC Locator.
    RestResult
    Save the results of one pass through the R-estimator algorithm.
    Station
    Keep all data for one seismic station here.
    StationID
    Station identifier (expanded station code).
    Stepper
    Manage the R-estimator logic needed to refine the hypocenter.
    Wresidual
    This weighted residuals storage combines the residuals and weights for picks and the Bayesian depth, while providing storage for the dispersion calculation and the spatial derivatives.
    ZoneStat
    Keep depth statistics for one Marsden square.
    ZoneStats
    Implements the historical free depth statistics portion of the SEDAS zone statistics subsystem.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    AuthorType
    Author types in the Hydra Locator interface are specified by integer constants from 1 to 4 with the meanings defined below.
    LocStatus
    Status and exit conditions.
